race.comment: FUSION BLAZER (4) goes very well at this journey here having never missed the frame including two wins. Missed the frame latest (19.03) when fifth over 320m at Richmond in a Grade 5. With a clean break looks hard to beat. MADAM ZELDA (3) goes very well at the course and distance with two wins and a placing from six starts. Below best last time at Richmond Straight (18.23) in a Grade 5, finishing a 9 length seventh. Can feature with the right run. SHUFFLE (7) isn't a quick beginner but comes home hard, finishing out of the frame two back but did wind up strongly to place when second (18.63) in a Grade 5 at this track. Expected to feature. BULLET THE BRUTE (8) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.
